text: Milutin Knežević (; 10 January 1949 – 30 March 2020) was a Serbian Orthodox prelate, Bishop of the Eparchy of Australia and New Zealand between 2003 and 2006, and the Eparchy of Valjevo from 2006 to 2020. He died on 30 March 2020, from problems due to COVID-19. He became first Eastern Orthodox bishop who died of COVID-19. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Serbian Orthodox priests Category:Eastern Orthodox bishops Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Belgrade
